Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced) into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Drain and rinse @Black Beans{13.4%oz}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{10%oz} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @Mexican Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Add tomato and scallion whites to #pot{}. Cook, stirring constantly, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with another pinch of salt and pepper.

Once veggies are softened, stir @Tomato Paste{1.5%oz} and @Sugar{1/4%tsp} into pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until combined, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{2%units}, @Cream Cheese{4%tbsp}, @Hot Sauce{1%tsp}, and @water{2.5%cups}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer, uncovered, ~{7%minutes}.

> Use 4 cups water and 15 minutes simmer for 4 servings.

Stir beans into pot. Simmer, uncovered, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide soup between bowls. Dollop with @Sour Cream{2%tbsp}. Garnish with @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup} and scallion greens. Serve.